observations.recommendation:
18.5 We recommended that Management:
a. establish responsibility center for GFPS under the Office of the Mayor;
b. direct the Municipal Accountant to provide RC code in the eNGAs;
c. direct the Municipal Budget Officer to provide RC code in the Budget.

We recommended that:
4. The Municipal Accountant obtain the necessary data from the Municipal Engineer, then prepare and maintain subsidiary ledger cards for Local Road Network, provide charge in maintaining the PPELC and depreciation separately to each component of the road network, submit a lapsing schedule for the computation of depreciation, and disclose the road network system in the Notes to Financial Statements in accordance with the prescribed format under COA Circular No. 2015-008;
5. The Municipal Mayor constitute a committee to conduct inventory of all road networks of the Municipality;
6. The Municipal Mayor tap other qualified personnel to fill-in the shoe of a regular GSO or create the position of GSO if funds warrant it; and
7. The Municipal Engineer provides the local accountant and the Supply Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.
